According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global polyethylene market was valued at USD 127.39 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 150.31 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 2.7% during the forecast period. Rising demand for flexible and rigid packaging, expanding infrastructure projects, increasing consumer goods production, and continuous innovations in recyclable and bio-based polyethylene are expected to drive market growth worldwide.
Polyethylene remains one of the world's most widely used thermoplastics due to its durability, lightweight properties, chemical resistance, and cost-effectiveness. Available in High-Density Polyethylene (HDPE), Low-Density Polyethylene (LDPE), and Linear Low-Density Polyethylene (LLDPE), the material serves a broad range of industries including packaging, construction, automotive, agriculture, healthcare, and consumer goods.
